---
/**
 * Why this matters — two-column editorial block. Library shelves portrait
 * left, the gap-in-the-market argument right. Background: bg-surface-card
 * with rule borders (per master plan).
 */
import Container from "@components/Container.astro";
import RemoteImage from "@components/RemoteImage.astro";
---

<section
  class="bg-surface-card border-y border-rule"
  aria-labelledby="why-this-matters-title"
>
  <Container width="wide" class="py-20 md:py-28 lg:py-32">
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 lg:gap-16 items-start">
      <div class="lg:col-span-5">
        <RemoteImage
          photoId="photo-1568992687947-868a62a9f521"
          alt="Library shelves with leather-bound volumes"
          aspect="portrait"
          width={900}
        />
      </div>

      <div class="lg:col-span-7 lg:pl-6 xl:pl-10">
        <p class="section-eyebrow">Why this matters</p>
        <h2
          id="why-this-matters-title"
          class="font-display font-normal text-display-lg text-surface-navy leading-[1.08] tracking-[-0.005em] text-balance"
          style='font-variation-settings: "opsz" 144;'
        >
          The gap in the market.
        </h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-[1.125rem] md:text-[1.1875rem] leading-[1.55] text-ink-muted text-pretty max-w-[36rem]">
          Estate planning software was built for mass-market families. Heritage Vault is the opposite.
        </p>

        <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 max-w-[36rem] text-[1.0625rem] leading-[1.7] text-ink">
          <p>
            Generic estate-planning tools target the mass-market family. One trust, one state, one generation, one ledger of beneficiaries. The product surface a national tool needs to ship for that audience is broad and shallow.
          </p>
          <p>
            UHNW families do not fit those tools. The estate carries a concentrated stock position. Property sits across multiple states, sometimes multiple jurisdictions. There are foreign assets, a second marriage, a dynasty trust written in 1994, a charitable remainder trust funded last year, an illiquid operating business that itself has its own governance.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Approach Book methodology has handled that level of complexity, family by family, for fifteen years. Heritage Vault is purpose-built for the same level. The platform now scales what the firm already proved by hand.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Container>
</section>
